(102, 'Benefits of a Facebook Business Page', 'Vizag', '<p>Facebook is the most popular social mediq network in the world, with more than 1.70 billion people using it every day for an average of 1 hour or a little less. With more&nbsp;than 80 percent small &amp; medium-sized businesses successfully running, Facebook serves as a perfect business platform to reach and connect with potential customers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here&rsquo;s a list of all the advantages of a facebook business page.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. You can expose your business to a global audience through the Facebook page, hence working on your brand development.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Display your products, posts, and ideas with your Facebook business page, and drive customers to your website.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Display your business in a positive light. Showcase your products and ideas in your posts to target your audience&rsquo;s interest. This will, in turn, help you generate leads for your business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Establish your communications with your clients via messages. And interact with your Facebook users through the medium of Facebook ads.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Get all your business insights with the Facebook page. For example, you can now look after your post reach and Facebook ad insights and plan for a better strategy for the future.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. The probability of engagements with potential clients inceases multi-folds on Facebook. Ad targeting allows you to build your audience on the Facebook business page.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7. Google&rsquo;s Facebook pages are automatically indexed; thus, published content may affect your site&rsquo;s overall results. Consider all the times you have looked for a company on Google and seen its Facebook page in the first few results. A link from your Facebook profile to your website may give some SEO benefits.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8. You can increase your social network by expanding your business across Facebook commerce surfaces like&nbsp;Facebook Shops, Drops, Page Shop, and&nbsp;Instagram Shopping. Advertising on Facebook or <a href=\"https://asetechnologies.in/\"><strong>Facebook Ad</strong></a> allows you to target certain demographics based on geography, age, gender, and users&rsquo; interests.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So if you haven&#39;t yet <a href=\"https://asetechnologies.in/\"><strong>created a Facebook business page</strong></a>, get in touch with us and we will do it for you. A Facebook business page is&nbsp;one of the best ways to connect with your customers and build a following for your company.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While Facebook began as a way for college students and other young adults to connect online, it has become a staple for businesses and community organizations. Social connections and genuine communication are integral parts of social media, and Facebook gives you an opportunity to attach a face, name, and personality to your brand. While your Facebook page may represent your company, it also allows you to show the human side of your business through one-on-one conversations, personal tidbits, and nonbusiness interaction.</p>\r\n', '19-September-2022', 'benefits-of-a-facebook-business-page', 'ase59.jpg', 'Facebook is the most popular social mediq network in the world, with more than 1.70 billion people using it every day', '', ''),
(103, 'Steps to Create Paid Social Media Campaigns', 'Vizag', '<p>Whether you want to generate brand awareness or you want to bring in more customers for your products or services, <strong><a href=\"https://asetechnologies.in/\">social media platform</a> </strong>is a great medium to advertise. Social ads can be hyper targeted, customers can interact with them, and you can easily adjust and adapt them based on data to make them more effective. Social networks will even reward you with lower costs and higher reach for getting people to engage with your ads.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Read these steps to nail the social media campaigns.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1. Start with an objective</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you start with a Paid advertisement the first thing you are asked is what is your objective. You must choose your objective carefully because your objective will directly affect your ad options. You have to choose from these three objective options - awareness objective, consideration objective, conversion objective. Objectives in the first option usually target reach, views or impressions, aiming to generate interest in your product or service. The second one centre around engagement or interaction aiming to seduce customers into searching for more information.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. Know Your audience</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>With a particular product or service you cannot target everybody through your advertisement. By narrowing down your target audience, you&rsquo;re able to be much smarter with your budget.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3. Pick the right social media platforms</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The earlier you know your objective and your audience the earlier you&#39;ll be able to choose the right social media network for your marketing campaign. Facebook has a wide range of both objectives and audience demographics which is why most of the businesses use Facebook as their Paid marketing campaign platform.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. Decide who you&#39;re targeting</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you&rsquo;ve decided which social platforms to use in your ad campaign, you can explore the detailed audience targeting options available to you on that platform. Because people click on or care about your ads when they are relevant. Targeting and retargeting help your ads find relevant audiences.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>5. Choose the best ad formats</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A social media platform gives you multiple ad formats aimed at same goal. Each type of ad has a different strength and you&rsquo;ll want to choose the right one, or combination of formats, to drive strong results for your paid campaign. If your product is visually appealing, consider creating content for image and video ads. If you&rsquo;re selling products, you can&rsquo;t go past carousels and collections alongside image or &lsquo;static&rsquo; ads and video ads.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>6. Create your campaign content</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Think about your ads. Now that you know what ad formats you want to use in your campaign, you have to nail down your copy, your photos, your video.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>7. Set your budget</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you&rsquo;ve chosen your objective and social media platform, you&rsquo;ll be able to research whether there&rsquo;s a&nbsp;minimum&nbsp;ad budget&nbsp;you&rsquo;re required to spend. This minimum amount could be per day, per click or per impression.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '27-September-2022', 'steps-to-create-paid-social-media-campaigns', 'asetech72.jpg', 'Whether you want to generate brand awareness or you want to bring in more customers for your products or services, social media platform is a great medium to advertise. ', '', ''),
